@startuml
title Timing Diagram Comprehensive Test

' ── All 6 Player Types ──
robust "Web Server" as WS #LightBlue
concise "Client" as C
clock "System Clock" as clk with period 10 pulse 5
binary "Enable" as EN
analog "Voltage" between 0 and 5 as V
rectangle "Status" as ST

' ── State Definitions ──
WS has Idle,Processing,Sending,Error
C has Waiting,Requesting,Receiving

' ── Absolute State Changes ──
@0
WS is Idle
C is Waiting
EN is low
V is 0
ST is Initializing

@10
WS is Processing
C is Requesting
EN is high
V is 3.5

@20
WS is Sending
C is Receiving
V is 4.2

@30
WS is Idle
C is Waiting
EN is low
V is 0
ST is Complete

' ── Player Context + Relative Time ──
@WS
40 is Error
+10 is Idle

' ── Named Time Point ──
@60 as :checkpoint

' ── Time Constraints ──
@0 <--> @10 : {10 ms}

' ── Inter-player Messages ──
C@10 --> WS@10 : request
WS@20 --> C@20 : response

' ── Highlights ──
highlight 10 to 20 #Gold : busy period

' ── Notes ──
note top of WS : Server handles requests
note bottom of C : Client state machine

' ── Compact Player ──
compact concise "Compact Client" as CC
@0
CC is Idle
@15
CC is Active
@30
CC is Idle

@enduml
